83
00:05:43,030 --> 00:05:46,390
Who said it'd take long if we followed the procedure?

84
00:05:49,090 --> 00:05:50,740
Huh?

85
00:05:54,240 --> 00:05:56,060
Yes, Chief Jang?

86
00:05:56,060 --> 00:05:58,760
I'll give you a security light number.

87
00:05:58,760 --> 00:06:01,420
Please report it broken.

88
00:06:01,420 --> 00:06:04,860
Okay. 10...

89
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:17,680
Hey.

90
00:06:17,680 --> 00:06:20,350
What? What is it? Are you still not done?

91
00:06:20,350 --> 00:06:22,050
Do you have to go receive the award?

92
00:06:22,050 --> 00:06:25,190
I won't, I won't! I won't do it out of spite.

93
00:06:25,190 --> 00:06:26,400
What is it, then?

94
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:30,180
I saw something today.

95
00:06:30,180 --> 00:06:31,480
But I'm confused about it.

96
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:35,300
I'm sorry, but I'm so tired.

97
00:06:35,300 --> 00:06:37,610
Can't we talk later?

98
00:06:40,980 --> 00:06:42,760
What's this?

99
00:06:42,760 --> 00:06:45,380
I suspect domestic violence.

100
00:06:45,380 --> 00:06:47,170
But?

101
00:06:48,480 --> 00:06:50,080
But it's a bit confusing.

102
00:06:50,080 --> 00:06:51,760
What is?

103
00:06:53,380 --> 00:06:57,320
She said she hurt herself doing the dishes.

104
00:07:01,580 --> 00:07:06,900
You don't have a husband, and you live with your son and his wife?

105
00:07:06,900 --> 00:07:11,710
Yes. By the way, who said that nonsense?

106
00:07:11,710 --> 00:07:15,540
Domestic violence? Seriously...

107
00:07:15,540 --> 00:07:16,910
I hope you understand.

108
00:07:16,910 --> 00:07:21,090
We need to check once we receive a report.

109
00:07:21,090 --> 00:07:23,550
I'm sorry,

110
00:07:23,550 --> 00:07:26,650
but what does your son do?

111
00:07:26,650 --> 00:07:29,960
He works at a trading company with his wife.

112
00:07:29,960 --> 00:07:32,760
You must be at home alone during the day, then.

113
00:07:32,760 --> 00:07:36,000
I guess I normally am.

114
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:38,910
Where did you hit yourself, by the way?

115
00:07:38,910 --> 00:07:42,630
Well, over... over there.

116
00:07:42,630 --> 00:07:46,040
I got dizzy getting up. So...

117
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:53,880
Is someone else at home?

118
00:07:53,880 --> 00:07:56,710
Yes. Y-Yes! The thing is...

119
00:07:56,710 --> 00:07:58,420
- Ma'am. Ms. Na.
- Ms. Na!

120
00:07:58,420 --> 00:08:01,440
- Why are you roaming around my house?
- It's okay. Stay with me.

121
00:08:01,440 --> 00:08:03,590
It's okay, it's okay.

122
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:35,190
Hi.

123
00:08:36,280 --> 00:08:38,440
What's your name?

124
00:08:41,490 --> 00:08:42,960
Do you want to come out for a second?

125
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:47,330
Grandma! Grandma!

126
00:08:48,140 --> 00:08:50,960
- Grandma!
- Goodness!

127
00:08:58,640 --> 00:08:59,540
My baby!

128
00:08:59,540 --> 00:09:02,800
Please check his body, Team Leader Kim.

129
00:09:07,020 --> 00:09:09,100
Grandma!

130
00:09:28,300 --> 00:09:32,380
[Wolsan Children's Welfare Center]

131
00:09:52,410 --> 00:09:54,760
Ms. Na is refusing to go to the shelter.

132
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:56,230
She's refusing to testify, too.

133
00:09:56,230 --> 00:10:00,890
I think it's best to keep monitoring her.

134
00:10:00,890 --> 00:10:02,750
Why is she refusing?

135
00:10:02,750 --> 00:10:04,320
It's common.

136
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:06,430
She doesn't want her son to get exposed.

137
00:10:06,430 --> 00:10:10,100
She's also insisting on dying by her son's side.

138
00:10:10,100 --> 00:10:11,430
How about the child?

139
00:10:11,430 --> 00:10:13,420
We should separate him from them, at least.

140
00:10:13,420 --> 00:10:15,720
He currently has extreme separation anxiety.

141
00:10:15,720 --> 00:10:20,520
Things will likely go badly if we separate him from his grandma.

142
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:23,480
We need to persuade Ms. Na first.

143
00:10:23,480 --> 00:10:25,880
This case is being transferred to the HQ now. Right?

144
00:10:25,880 --> 00:10:27,100
Yes.

145
00:10:27,100 --> 00:10:29,370
Thank you, Chief.

146
00:10:29,370 --> 00:10:30,770
Thank you.

147
00:10:30,770 --> 00:10:33,380
What if something goes wrong with her before we persuade her?

148
00:10:33,380 --> 00:10:35,230
What will happen to the child, then?

149
00:10:35,230 --> 00:10:36,690
That's enough, Team Leader Kim.

150
00:10:36,690 --> 00:10:39,280
Can we at least get an update—

151
00:10:39,280 --> 00:10:41,610
I definitely warned you.

152
00:10:44,610 --> 00:10:47,620
I heard you recently caused mayhem at

153
00:10:47,620 --> 00:10:51,030
the child protection agency and Namchon Police Station.

154
00:10:51,030 --> 00:10:53,110
Regarding a child abuse case.

155
00:10:53,110 --> 00:10:56,480
Lieutenant Kim, let's not cross the line here.

156
00:10:56,480 --> 00:10:58,210
Don't go any further.

157
00:10:58,210 --> 00:11:00,040
Well, then...

158
00:11:11,710 --> 00:11:14,410
You think you're always right, don't you?

159
00:11:14,410 --> 00:11:18,840
You don't even care what your colleagues think, do you?

160
00:11:19,940 --> 00:11:21,240
I feel the same way.

161
00:11:21,240 --> 00:11:25,040
I don't care about what you think, either.

162
00:11:43,310 --> 00:11:46,560
Hey! What happened? What happened?

163
00:11:47,160 --> 00:11:50,160
Well, she was abused.

164
00:11:50,160 --> 00:11:52,990
Good work, Mom. We owe you.

165
00:11:54,490 --> 00:11:57,580
- Is that it?
- Of course, it is.

166
00:11:58,330 --> 00:12:01,780
I couldn't be interested even if I wanted to. It's no longer our case.

167
00:12:01,780 --> 00:12:04,530
How could you say that as a cop?

168
00:12:05,990 --> 00:12:08,740
We each have our own job. What can I do?

169
00:12:08,740 --> 00:12:11,420
What kind of cop are you?

170
00:12:13,080 --> 00:12:14,380
Why are you doing this now?

171
00:12:14,380 --> 00:12:16,900
How far am I supposed to go?

172
00:12:17,570 --> 00:12:21,400
What do you mean? All the way to the end!

173
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:25,290
I already did everything I could!

174
00:12:25,290 --> 00:12:28,840
The case is being transferred. What am I supposed to do?

175
00:12:31,840 --> 00:12:35,580
If you're not done insulting, finish it up and go inside.

176
00:12:37,710 --> 00:12:40,640
Was there any child there?

177
00:12:40,640 --> 00:12:43,590
A boy around five or six years old.

178
00:12:50,220 --> 00:12:52,000
How did you know?

179
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:54,180
Was he abused, too?

180
00:12:54,180 --> 00:12:56,050
Why didn't you tell me there'd be a child?

181
00:12:56,050 --> 00:12:58,860
I wouldn't have wandered if you told me in advance!

182
00:12:58,860 --> 00:13:01,580
Kids get scared when a lot of people show up.

183
00:13:01,580 --> 00:13:04,590
They just hide somewhere!

184
00:13:04,590 --> 00:13:08,620
It's so scary when a bunch of adults come while talking.

185
00:13:17,580 --> 00:13:19,810
We're done taking care of it.

186
00:13:19,810 --> 00:13:23,240
The people from the child protection agency came

187
00:13:23,240 --> 00:13:28,140
and it's already halfway done since the case was exposed to the law.

188
00:13:28,140 --> 00:13:30,380
You said they still live together!

189
00:13:30,380 --> 00:13:33,920
With that father, son, or that bastard! Is that taking care of it?

190
00:13:33,920 --> 00:13:36,930
What do you want me to do, exactly?

191
00:13:46,080 --> 00:13:47,930
I...

192
00:14:51,420 --> 00:14:54,620
He's the one who told me to stop.

193
00:15:20,750 --> 00:15:22,930
- Welcome!
- Hello!

194
00:15:22,930 --> 00:15:25,660
- Kim Jin Hee! Kim Jin Hee! Kim Jin Hee!
- You came.

195
00:15:25,660 --> 00:15:28,250
- A draft beer, please!
- Okay.

196
00:15:28,250 --> 00:15:30,350
Hey, have you been well?

197
00:15:30,350 --> 00:15:32,340
You think I have?

198
00:15:32,340 --> 00:15:35,170
How could he send me to this police station without any mention?

199
00:15:35,170 --> 00:15:39,840
Hey, Senior Eun Ji Won apparently was sent there because he got demoted!

200
00:15:43,730 --> 00:15:45,880
I suspected it, but it's still surprising.

201
00:15:45,880 --> 00:15:47,270
Right?

202
00:15:47,270 --> 00:15:49,660
He was so well-connected, and he was so doing so well!

203
00:15:49,660 --> 00:15:52,890
I thought he'd keep climbing the ladder and never leave the HQ.

204
00:15:52,890 --> 00:15:56,130
This is why you never know what'd happen to people.

205
00:15:56,130 --> 00:15:58,850
Hey. He apparently got demoted for defiance.

206
00:15:58,850 --> 00:16:00,570
What? Defiance?

207
00:16:00,570 --> 00:16:03,990
Yes, to the higher-ups, even. Do you believe that?

208
00:16:03,990 --> 00:16:05,890
- About what?
- I don't know!

209
00:16:05,890 --> 00:16:09,740
None of his colleagues even knew much about it!

210
00:16:10,410 --> 00:16:13,580
I don't know what happened, but something must've happened.

211
00:16:13,580 --> 00:16:16,360
He became so venomous.

212
00:16:16,360 --> 00:16:20,150
Hey! Venomous, my foot!

213
00:16:20,150 --> 00:16:26,070
He must be pretty difficult and a perfectionist when it comes to work.

214
00:16:26,070 --> 00:16:30,410
But he's so friendly and sweet to people

215
00:16:30,410 --> 00:16:33,060
and he had such a pretty smile!

216
00:16:33,060 --> 00:16:34,500
I see...

217
00:16:34,500 --> 00:16:35,650
Did he smile at you?

218
00:16:35,650 --> 00:16:36,790
Of course!

219
00:16:36,790 --> 00:16:39,410
He never smiled at me even once.

220
00:16:40,120 --> 00:16:43,420
Well, what does that mean?

221
00:16:44,110 --> 00:16:45,490
Did he like me by chance?

222
00:16:45,490 --> 00:16:48,370
Gosh. Here we go again. Here we go again.

223
00:16:48,370 --> 00:16:50,530
He must've.

224
00:16:50,530 --> 00:16:51,910
I knew it.

225
00:16:51,910 --> 00:16:54,220
You're basically delusional at this point.

226
00:16:54,220 --> 00:16:56,140
No wonder...

227
00:16:56,140 --> 00:17:00,690
I should've been more observant. Right?

228
00:17:00,690 --> 00:17:02,990
Gosh, why did it have to be me?

229
00:17:02,990 --> 00:17:04,780
I wasn't so bad then. Right?

230
00:17:04,780 --> 00:17:07,180
Getting fired and

231
00:17:07,180 --> 00:17:10,080
getting demoted.

232
00:17:10,080 --> 00:17:12,130
They love doing that.

233
00:17:12,130 --> 00:17:14,420
What is it, an exile?

234
00:17:20,010 --> 00:17:23,260
Who said it'd take long if we follow the procedure?

235
00:17:24,540 --> 00:17:27,360
He was right. They fixed it quickly.

236
00:17:31,330 --> 00:17:33,630
It's still a bit dark.

237
00:18:37,260 --> 00:18:42,890
[Namchon Police Station]

238
00:18:53,650 --> 00:18:55,750
Does anyone want coffee?

239
00:19:00,270 --> 00:19:03,580
Oh, no. I guess I asked too late.

240
00:19:16,110 --> 00:19:18,040
Oh, Chief Jang!

241
00:19:18,040 --> 00:19:21,660
The complaint about the broken security light.

242
00:19:21,660 --> 00:19:25,210
I was surprised that it got fixed quicker than I thought.

243
00:19:25,210 --> 00:19:27,800
What are you talking about?

244
00:19:27,800 --> 00:19:29,700
You haven't checked yet.

245
00:19:29,700 --> 00:19:33,260
It was already fixed. Wasn't it fast?

246
00:19:39,240 --> 00:19:41,900
It hasn't been fixed yet.

247
00:19:41,900 --> 00:19:43,330
Pardon?

248
00:19:44,060 --> 00:19:47,420
I saw that it was lit last night.

249
00:19:51,750 --> 00:19:54,200
Huh? Who's the person in charge?

250
00:19:54,200 --> 00:19:56,770
[Complaint result]
Why are they doing it like this?

251
00:19:58,290 --> 00:20:00,330
There's a triple collision in front of Daehan Bank.

252
00:20:00,330 --> 00:20:03,430
They want us to send as many cars as possible.

253
00:20:03,430 --> 00:20:05,590
See you later.

254
00:20:05,590 --> 00:20:07,330
Let's go.

255
00:20:20,750 --> 00:20:24,540
D-Did they want m-me to come, too?

256
00:20:26,100 --> 00:20:28,950
- Yes, Ms. Kim.
- Yes, you reached the hospital.

257
00:20:28,950 --> 00:20:32,380
Pardon? Physical therapist?

258
00:20:36,840 --> 00:20:38,660
Who is it?

259
00:20:38,660 --> 00:20:40,610
I don't know.

260
00:20:42,280 --> 00:20:44,630
Yes, this is she!

261
00:20:44,630 --> 00:20:47,850
Are you the one who reported my mother?

262
00:20:47,850 --> 00:20:51,870
Why get involved in our family business without knowing anything?

263
00:20:51,870 --> 00:20:54,100
I'm finding a lawyer right now.

264
00:20:54,100 --> 00:20:56,550
Slander and libel.

265
00:20:56,550 --> 00:20:58,560
I'll charge you with everything I can.

